[Student "S"]
{NORTH has a minimum 1\S opening bid - 13 points and five trumps. She doesn't even suspect 
what's about to befall!

SOUTH hears the 1\S bid and all he wants to know is whether NORTH has one, two or three Aces. 
So he uses the Blackwood convention, 4NT.

NORTH has two Aces so she bids 5\H (5\C would show zero Aces, 
5\D would show one Ace, etc).

SOUTH has heard enough and bids 6\S.}

